# Project standards

- Use Java 21 features where they improve clarity
- Use Spring Boot conventions and constructor injection
- Keep classes small and single-purpose
- Prefer records for request/response DTOs
- All Java classes must be under package `com.dfs.dfsguard`
- Use package structure exactly as described in `docs/01-architecture.md`
- Use meaningful names like `PolicyEngine`, `GuardService`, `ApprovalService`
- Avoid unnecessary layers or generic abstractions
- All externally visible APIs must have request/response DTOs
- All security-sensitive decisions must produce audit events
- Add or update tests when changing security logic
